comment: LATR and LHH show that Turner (IND) maintains a legal guarding position and Mahinmi (IND) cleanly strips the ball from Love (CLE). Any body to body contact on the play is initiated by Love.
Turner (IND) maintains a legal guarding position on the drive by Dellavedova (CLE) and does not affect his RSBQ.
Hill (IND) makes incidental contact with Irving (CLE) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Dellavedova (CLE) firms up as he sets the screen on George (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
James (CLE) establishes a legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with George's (IND) non-shooting arm that does not affect the driving layup attempt.
Stuckey (IND) does not establish a legal guarding position prior to the contact with James (CLE).
George (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Thompson (CLE) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Dellavedova (CLE) retreats and maintains a legal guarding position on the drive to the basket and shot attempt by Ellis (IND).
Dellavedova (CLE) makes incidental contact with Hill (IND) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on Irving (CLE).
Hill (IND) commits a take foul on Irving (CLE).
